porter /ˈpɔːtə/

(porters) 

1. N-COUNT A porter is a person whose job is to carry things, for example, people's luggage at a train station or in a hotel. 搬运工 

例： Our taxi pulled up at Old Delhi station and a porter sprinted to the door. 我们的出租车停在老德里车站，一个搬运工疾步跑向车门。 

2. N-COUNT In a hospital, a porter is someone whose job is to move patients from place to place. (医院里的)护工 [英国英语] 

3. N-COUNT A porter is a person whose job is to be in charge of the entrance of a building such as a hotel. 门童 [英国英语] 

4. N a dark sweet ale brewed from black malt (用烤麦酿制的)黑啤酒 [英国英语]

